{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491343","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491343"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:43:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:43:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"917"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/917"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.03,0.15,0.25,0.41]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"917"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102852"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"917","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/917"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"917"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85318"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"461"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"3376"},{"type":"tags","id":"3455"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"9802"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"201"},{"type":"contributions","id":"872"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7220"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13170"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14852"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15891"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18299"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35950"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36014"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38759"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45090"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102852","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102852"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old man presents with a three month history of pain on swallowing. This is on a background of gastro-oesophageal reflux, the latter which has been present for many years. An endoscopy shows an area of ulceration with two areas of nodularity in a segment of Barrett\u0027s epithelium. Surrounding inflammation extends up to the mid-oesophagus. Focussed biopsies are taken of the nodular areas and these show metaplastic columnar-lined epithelium with areas of high-grade dysplasia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Repeat endoscopy and biopsies","pH and manometric studies","Esomeprazole and repeat endoscopy in three months","CT chest and abdomen","Argon ablation therapy"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of a well-defined ulcer, nodularity and high grade dysplasia in an area of Barrett\u0027s epithelium raises strong suspicions of oesophageal malignancy. The length of the area of inflammation also increases the risk of malignant change. \u003Cstrong\u003EFurther endoscopy and biopsies\u003C/strong\u003E of the ulcerated and nodular areas must be done. This further endoscopy should be done at a tertiary specialist centre, where the Seattle Protocol will be applied. This protocol involves taking four-quadrant biopsies every 1-2 cm along the Barrett\u0027s segment, plus biopsies of any visible mucosal irregularities. The goal is to increase the chances of detecting dysplasia or early cancer in the oesophagus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis will help determine treatment. Depending what the histology of these biopsies show, there could be potentially endoscopic therapy (endoscopic mucosal resection) or surgery. Ablation therapy should only be done if frank malignancy is excluded. A single set of biopsies showing high grade dysplasia (HGD) would not be sufficient. Argon beam ablation is usually reserved for when any HGD/pT1a disease has been removed by endoscopic mucosal resection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis patient may require a proton pump inhibitor for control of their gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD), however this can not be done in isolation. Esomeprazole alone is inappropriate without further investigation. Manometric and ph studies are not helpful as GORD is already diagnosed. Whilst a CT chest/abdomen will likely be done if the presence of malignancy is confirmed, the most important investigation is the repeat endoscopy and biopsy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["An area of ulceration in Barrett\u0027s oesophagus must raise the concern of malignancy."],"references":["Whiteman, DC, Kendall, BJ. Barrett\u2019s oesophagus: epidemiology, diagnosis and clinical management. MJA. 2016 October 3; 205(7): 317-324. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27681974/","Iyer PG, Chak A. Surveillance in Barrett\u2019s Esophagus: Challenges, Progress, and Possibilities. Gastroenterology 2023; 164:707\u201318"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85318"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"917"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85318"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-16T15:35:23+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-12T16:19:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"917"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102852"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tag